    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-09-01T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-09-01T17:00:00-05:00" n="542"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d542">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">784A.02/8–3150: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Israel</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-09-01T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 1, 1950—6 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>94. Ur 123 Aug 31. Dept regrets inadvertence not discussing question Jerusalem
                    with McGrath and commends <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> for manner in
                    which McGrath’s official visit handled with Israeli Govt.</p>
                <p>With regard Palmer’s visits in Jerusalem, point made by <gloss
                        target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> spokesman is not valid since Palmer
                    member of <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> Comm whose seat is Jerusalem by
                    virtue <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> Res establishing <gloss
                        target="#t_PCC1">PCC</gloss>.</p>
                <p>View difficulties being encountered by <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> Dept
                    willing consider modification position but reluctant make any major changes
                    prior consideration Jerusalem question by Fifth <gloss target="#t_GA1"
                        >GA</gloss>. What modification wld <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss>
                    recommend? What is current practice other missions Tel Aviv re dealings with
                    Israeli Govt officials in Jerusalem?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
